column2: While addressing others' needs you are: Inflexible and stick to your needs
While addressing others' needs you are: Flexible and alter your needs to make others happy
You are self sufficient in the sense : Completely independent of others
You are self sufficient in the sense : Interdependent and connected with others
In your dealings you :  Overcome your personal terms and follow principles to do what is right
In your dealings you :  Prefer personal terms, sometimes not going by principles
Your drive to improve comes from: Inner critic to do what is judged as right
Your drive to improve comes from: Drive to succeed and be recognized for your accomplishments
In the process of achieving a goal : You find the method to do it perfectly and stick to it until it succeeds
In the process of achieving a goal : You find the most efficient/ fastest possible method and in case it doesnot work , you change the method quickly to achieve the desired result
While irritated or emotionally disturbed at work You tend to express your emotions openly and people are easily aware of it
While irritated or emotionally disturbed at work You are not usually distracted by your feelings without people being aware of your emotional state
You tend to Suppress personal desires and become self constrained
You tend to Experience strong personal desires to the point of being self-absorbed (disconnected from outside world)
You Focus on responsibilities before emotions
You Sort out emotions and then complete duties effectively
You get irritated of others when They are inefficient ,sloppy
You get irritated of others when They are insensitive to oneself and you
You tend to suppress your desires or detach from feelings to To improve yourself and others
You tend to suppress your desires or detach from feelings to To protect yourself from being intruded and conserve your energy
You tend to judge people on Activities governed by their internal standards of right and wrong
You tend to judge people on Intellectual matters,knowledge and competence
How do you deal with people who you think are wrong or whom you do not like you are convinced why you are correct and make efforts to make people understand that
How do you deal with people who you think are wrong or whom you do not like You are not certain about your views and do not worry much if they do not agree with your view
How do you prevent yourself from committing mistakes?  Comparing things to find out what is correct in order to avoid criticism
How do you prevent yourself from committing mistakes?  Doubting and trying to find out the potential threats in order to gain sense of safety and security
While taking decisions you are Mostly sure and have one right way of doing something
While taking decisions you are generally unsure of the way to take and consider many ways of doing something
How do you deal with your negative feelings You can control negative feelings and keep negative feelings at bay
How do you deal with your negative feelings You find it difficult to ignore negative feelings
How do you deal with your desires? You are self restrained and limit your desires
How do you deal with your desires? You are are fun loving and strongly dislike limits on your desires
How do you like to lead your life? Be self controlled,focussed , do not like to deviate from careful preparations/plans and particular about time and procedures,reserved
How do you like to lead your life? Be adventurous,spontaneous, follow your inspiration and do not like to stick to plans,not particular about procedures,open minded,flexible
How do you perceive your future? You know your mission clearly and have set high standards for achieving it , thus expect to be disappointed,practical
How do you perceive your future? Your mission is a feeling/desire and you hope that you will achieve it , think positive,optimistic
How do you deal with anger? You suppress anger and shows it when you think it is right
How do you deal with anger? You express your anger on the spot and openly
What according to you makes people agree to your views/how do you do it? You put logical reasons and arguments and try to convince them
What according to you makes people agree to your views/how do you do it? You rely on your self confidence and sheer personality,engaging them with gusty conversations
What is the first step in establishing justice according to you? To reward those who do good and punish the wrongdoers.
What is the first step in establishing justice according to you? To establish equality in terms of power/authority
You Are not easily convinced to take a break,do not allow yourself to be unproductive
You Are easily convinced to take a break from work which will be useful
You Do not compromise with your principles to avoid conflicts
You Do not want to get into conflicts with your loved ones and hold on your strong opinions to yourself
You Hold on to your principles and ideals, always want to improve others and press for change
You Go along with others agendas and are more adaptable to their views and often lose sight of your own view
Your focus is primarily on: Relationships and others’ needs and feelings
Your focus is primarily on: Tasks and on completing goals
What type of relationships do you prefer Close and intimate
What type of relationships do you prefer Ordinary relationships, close relationships make you uncomfortable at times
People are attracted towards you because of Your friendly nature and that you give attention to their feelings
People are attracted towards you because of Your outstanding way of work and dealing with things
You Tend to move towards others and engage them
You Tend to withdraw from others hoping they would seek you
You Look for people to rescue them
You Look for someone to rescue you
You focus on and are aware of Others’ feelings and unaware of your needs
You focus on and are aware of Your feelings and fail to recognize your impact on others
You are Emotionally expressive and people oriented
You are Emotionally detached and loners
If you are rejected by people you cope by Winning over them
If you are rejected by people you cope by Detaching and isolating yourself
Which one do you appreciate more in people Feelings
Which one do you appreciate more in people Intellectual approaches and conceptual thinking
In a relationship you want Love and sense of self worth
In a relationship you want Certainty and security
What do you want more To be loved and to be important to others
What do you want more Approval and support of others
In a new relationship or friendship you Welcome others and focus on their feelings, sometimes losing on your feelings
In a new relationship or friendship you Welcome others but also doubt thems and protect yourself
You orient primarily towards Others needs, feelings and wants and alter yourself to meet them
You orient primarily towards Your feelings and likes and want to pursue them
With respect to expressing your feelings You do not easily express anger and do not show wide range of feeling which are short lived
With respect to expressing your feelings Your feelings are quite short lived and you display wide range of emotions like anger, frustration, delight or excitement
If a relationship is not working You try to rework and find it difficult to let go
If a relationship is not working You don’t like clinging on and feel letting go is better
You tend to focus on others and empower them based on Their feelings and wants; altering your beliefs
You tend to focus on others and empower them based on Your sense of justice that you feel is important
While not happy about something You find it difficult to show your feelings or anger and use indirect approaches
While not happy about something You directly communicate your aggression or disappointment
When you are frustrated You tend to make others feel guilty of it may be by dramatizing the suffering
When you are frustrated You push hard to get what you want may be by using direct threats
While mingling with people You tend to alter your views/opinions ( lose your real self) to be accepted and sometimes become over friendly
While mingling with people You are welcoming but do not alter your opinions to be accepted and also do not invade in people’s personal space
While focussing on others’ needs and feelings You want a bit of appreciation and love from others
While focussing on others’ needs and feelings Attention or appreciation from others do not matter much may be because you want to be independent and safe from their influence
While in conflicts You tend to remind others how much they are indebted to you for your help
While in conflicts You tend to become silent or avoid further conflicts
You Are able to easily focus on your goals by letting go off your feelings or desires
You Are not able to focus on your goals and find it difficult to let go off your feelings and desires
While feeling emotional at work you Focus your task and are able to ignore your feelings
While feeling emotional at work you First need time to sort out your feelings and then proceed working
Most of the time you find yourself to be Socially confident with positive self-image
Most of the time you find yourself to be Socially uncomfortable with underconfident self image
You Are always up for work and work is more continuous for you with little or no breaks at all so that you are not perceived as sluggish
You Are energetic in intervals with distinct periods of withdrawal and recharge yourselves by thinking things over

You engage yourself in any task / subject To take it as a stepping stone to achieve your final goal and are quick to change your subject if it does not give you success or contribute in your final goal.

You engage yourself in any task / subject To acquire knowledge and learn and do not care about the final goal in doing so; also you will not stop doing a particular thing until you or the subject or both are exhausted by its content
You Care about having a good self image ( both looks and intellect) and work towards maintaining it
You Do not care about how you look or are seen as and follow your mind to acquire knowledge and do your work
You Are self mobilised to work towards your set goal to achieve appreciation and recognition and like them
You Are reluctant to start working as you are uncertain of your goal and fear pitfalls and are uncomfortable with appreciation and recognition and doubt them
You Want to be in the front ,known by all and in the limelight
You Do not want to be in the spotlight because with fame comes the fear of being blamed later for things that go wrong
Choose the one which describes you more  Success oriented and optimistic
Choose the one which describes you more  Security oriented and generally pessimistic
You Focus on your set goal and ignore your own pleasures in order to achieve success and maintain a good self image
You Focus on your own pleasures and desires and believe in keeping your options open in order to to achieve personal entitlement
You Focus on receiving constant stimulation, making worthwhile experiences and feel happy without any tendency to showing it off to anyone
You Focus on showing others that you are having a good time and might want others to feel jealous about it
You project the following image Cool, self controlled, perfectly together, without any problems
You project the following image Do not censor yourself and are funny, unrestricted, may be impulsive
You see failure As a personal humiliation and dread failures
You see failure As an opportunity to learn and do not highly fear failing
For you Success and recognition is more important than power and authority
For you Power and authority is more important than success and recognition
You are Highly competitive and do not argue with people to prove that you are right (conscious of your image)
You are Self assertive and argue with people to come to the right point
You Are fast paced, efficient , focussed and are impatient when obstruction comes their way in terms of others views, opinions etc
You Are slow paced,readily welcome others opinions and views and also may substitute their agendas over yours
You Are a self starter and take initiative to do things
You Find it difficult to self start and seek others to keep you motivated
You Want to seek attention of people who are important to you and work to get that
You You feel it is awkward to ask for attention and distant yourself easily.
You are: Emotional and okay with sharing your feelings with others with less personal boundaries preferred
You are: Do not feel like sharing your emotions with many people and want to keep clear personal boundaries, might feel detached sometime
Your work includes more of Imagination and fantasies, may be about you, your close relatives or based on your experiences
Your work includes more of What you observe or see around, may be based on experiments. more about reality less autobiographical.
To understand yourself or others You try to undertstand the feelings or emotions
To understand yourself or others You try to comprehend the logics
For you, It is okay to indulge into feelings and longings and think deeply about them to see what is missing that could be fulfilled
For you, One should not be trapped in feelings and longings and think about what might go wrong in doing so
Choose I am generally alone in life as I find it difficult to form bonds with others
Choose I can make bonds with others but I fear losing them
Which is more likely to make you depressed When you find that you have lost an opportunity to work on your dreams
Which is more likely to make you depressed When you make your higher authority angry or disappointed with you
You tend to: Become gloomy and think deeply about emotions, even accepting negative emotions as a part of life
You tend to: Be happy and avoid pain or negative feelings
You tend to take back memories (eg. a momento) from trips because: It makes you appreciate the beauty of the place or appreciate the momento you bring with you

You tend to take back memories (eg. a momento) from trips because: It becomes a possession which helps you recall your accomplishment of going to that place, beauty of the object doesn’t matter much but experience does
What happens when you get a thing that you wanted to have for too long (eg. shoes, jeans, mobile phone) You are excited and able to appreciate the beauty and possession for quite long
What happens when you get a thing that you wanted to have for too long (eg. shoes, jeans, mobile phone) You are excited initially but soon lose interest and want to have something else very soon
You tend to Focus on your feelings that might lead to inactivity or losing direction
You tend to Overcome feeling to focus on work leading to neglection of your feelings at times
While dealing with feelings of hurt or loneliness You find it difficult to let go of them and find it okay to take help of others to overcome
While dealing with feelings of hurt or loneliness You think taking help would make you dependent on others and you yourself can get over it
You would describe yourself as  Soft, vulnerable, express emotions
You would describe yourself as  Tough, strong, repress emotions
You tend to withdraw yourself from people: To protect yourself and give some time to yourself to deal with your emotions
You tend to withdraw yourself from people: If you find them threatening or if they make you upset
What is true about you You deal with all realities of life like tragedy, sadness, discomfort or happiness
What is true about you You want the world to be happy and at peace, you find comfort in ordinary lives
Choose one you can better relate to most of the time Pessimistic, moody and negative
Choose one you can better relate to most of the time Optimistic, easy-going and positive
While dealing with negative feelings You detach from your feelings and delay your response to them
While dealing with negative feelings You magnify the danger and react immediately (often intensely) most of the times and find it difficult to detach from your feelings
To come to conclusions: You trust your own minds more than others
To come to conclusions: You try to find something to trust as you find it difficult to go by your mind alone
Choose the one which describes you best Eccentric, ignore rules and seek knowledge
Choose the one which describes you best Relate to tradition, consider rules and seek security
You tend to Withdraw yourself from others and you can spend hours alone, reading books, listening to music or working on your project
You tend to Stay active, might work with dedication but gets irritated sitting for too long

You tend to Be optimistic and avoid dark or painful side of life

You Generally act before thinking much

Describe yourself  Insensitive, aggressive and often feel powerful

You tend to Find it difficult to detach from others rather blend with them to keep life comfortable and peaceful

Which describes you better Optimistic but irresponsible sometimes, forgetful and want freedom

You want  Intensity, control and power
